<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-218-038 </DOCNO><DOCID>10 440 242</DOCID><JOURNAL>San Jose Mercury News  Feb 25 1991 p6D(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Saddam: captain of industry. (computer-generated view of SaddamHussein) (product announcement)andM;</TITLE><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Mind Profiles Laboratory Inc, which makes computer programs foruse in employee screening, introduces Prophesy ($36.95), asoftware program that claims to predict an individual's futureactions with 78 percent accuracy.andP;  Prophesy was run to generate aprofile of Iraqi Pres Saddam Hussein.andP;  The profile describesSaddam as being intense, single-minded and ruthless.andP;  Saddam issaid to be someone who might challenge the strong while crushingthe weak.andP;  Bob Dean, president of Mind Profiles, characterizesSaddam as a person who probably would employ others to do 'dirtywork,' eliminating those so employed afterwards.andP;  Prophesy doeswhat it does by reviewing answers to 27 questions, comparinganswers to a data base of behavioral situations.andP;  The software,which sells by mail, runs on IBM-or-compatible microcomputers.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Mind Profiles Laboratory Inc. (Product introduction).andO;Product:   Prophecy (Computer game) (Product introduction).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionPsychology.andO;Person:    Dean, Bob (Attitudes).andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>